write('README.md',`# 1099TaxCalcs.com — Phase 1\n\nA static, privacy-conscious calculator site built with HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript for GitHub Pages.\n\n## Structure\n\n- \`index.html\`: homepage and quick estimate\n- \`calculators/\`: directory plus six calculator pages\n- \`guides/\`, \`deductions/\`, \`states/\`: educational directories\n- Legal, about, contact, editorial, and methodology folders\n- \`assets/css/styles.css\`: shared responsive and print styles\n- \`assets/js/main.js\`: navigation and print behavior\n- \`assets/js/calculators.js\`: validation, shared formulas, and central tax configuration\n- \`robots.txt\`, \`sitemap.xml\`, and \`404.html\`: discovery and error support\n\n## Local preview\n\nFrom this directory, run a simple static server such as \`python -m http.server 8000\`, then visit \`http://localhost:8000/\`. Opening files directly also works for the site’s relative assets and links, though a server best matches GitHub Pages.\n\n## Calculator assumptions\n\nAll calculations run in the browser. Federal constants are centralized in \`TAX_CONFIG\` at the top of \`assets/js/calculators.js\`. Results are simplified planning estimates rounded to whole dollars for display. User-entered rates are not verified by the site. See \`methodology/index.html\` and each calculator’s assumptions and limitations.\n\n## Annual tax-review checklist\n\nBefore publication and at least annually, verify against authoritative current sources:\n\n1. Self-employment taxable earnings percentage.\n2. Social Security and Medicare rates and the Social Security wage base.\n3. Additional Medicare rate and filing-status thresholds.\n4. Mileage rate for each applicable tax year.\n5. Home-office simplified rate and square-foot limit.\n6. Estimated-tax safe harbors, payment dates, forms, and instructions.\n7. Federal brackets, deductions, credits, and contribution limits before adding them.\n8. State and local rates, thresholds, filing rules, and deadlines.\n9. Legal, privacy, advertising, accessibility, and editorial content.\n\nNo CNAME is created or modified by the Phase 1 generator.\n`);

